00:12:34,855 --> 00:12:36,957
I've hardly been a monk.

247
00:12:37,024 --> 00:12:39,459
Forget that she knows Jane.

248
00:12:39,526 --> 00:12:42,128
This girl's terrific.
She looks like Virginia Mayo.

249
00:12:42,196 --> 00:12:44,898
She's 25, mount Holyoke
gymnastics team.

250
00:12:44,965 --> 00:12:47,267
See her this weekend.

251
00:12:47,335 --> 00:12:50,003
You hit it off,
come Turkey day maybe
you can stuff her.

252
00:12:57,045 --> 00:12:59,346
Sweetheart,
8:00 Saturday night,

253
00:12:59,414 --> 00:13:01,648
Jimmy's la grange
for beauty and the beast.

254
00:13:01,716 --> 00:13:03,985
- Roger.
- They have chicken Kiev.

255
00:13:04,052 --> 00:13:06,420
The butter squirts everywhere.

256
00:13:18,001 --> 00:13:20,569
- Hello, Mr. Draper.
- Hello, Celia.

257
00:13:27,376 --> 00:13:30,678
I made you some pork chops.
They're good cold too.

258
00:13:30,746 --> 00:13:33,047
I look forward to it.

259
00:13:33,114 --> 00:13:35,749
But you don't eat nothing.

260
00:13:38,118 --> 00:13:41,020
- Have you seen my shine Kit?
- I put it on the top
of the closet.

261
00:13:41,088 --> 00:13:43,222
<i>- the children coming
this weekend?</i>

262
00:13:43,290 --> 00:13:44,990
No.

263
00:13:45,058 --> 00:13:48,227
You need to put things
back where you found them.

264
00:13:48,294 --> 00:13:50,896
I didn't want to leave it
in the middle of the floor.

265
00:14:04,177 --> 00:14:06,612
Okay, good night.
You have a good weekend.

266
00:14:06,680 --> 00:14:08,648
And eat something.

267
00:14:37,874 --> 00:14:40,509
Let me out of here!

268
00:14:40,576 --> 00:14:43,711
Let me out of here!

269
00:14:45,047 --> 00:14:47,848
<i>Let me out of here!</i>

270
00:14:49,917 --> 00:14:52,052
Footprints on a wet floor...

271
00:14:52,119 --> 00:14:54,221
That's no longer
a hanging offense.

272
00:14:54,288 --> 00:14:57,223
<i>Glo-coat's
patented formula</i>

273
00:14:57,291 --> 00:14:59,759
<i>Goes on easy
and dries in seconds.</i>

274
00:16:03,751 --> 00:16:06,318
So how do you know Jane?

275
00:16:06,386 --> 00:16:09,789
Before you ask me all
the questions, you have
to let me finish one glass.

276
00:16:11,524 --> 00:16:13,726
<i>I don't have to ask you
any questions.</i>

277
00:16:15,461 --> 00:16:17,662
I think I'm actually nervous.

278
00:16:17,730 --> 00:16:20,230
I haven't done this
since college.

279
00:16:20,298 --> 00:16:23,233
Not that it was so long ago,
although it seems like it.

280
00:16:23,301 --> 00:16:25,435
I borrowed a dress.

281
00:16:25,503 --> 00:16:28,204
You sat down so fast
I didn't get a good look.

282
00:16:28,272 --> 00:16:29,639
Do you want to see it?

283
00:16:44,921 --> 00:16:46,789
I can't believe I did that.

284
00:16:48,892 --> 00:16:51,160
It's hard to believe
there are two girls
who can wear that.

285
00:16:53,197 --> 00:16:55,732
Don, I want to lift
a shadow off this evening.

286
00:16:55,799 --> 00:16:58,534
I know this is your first date.

287
00:16:58,602 --> 00:17:00,603
First that Roger
was involved in.

288
00:17:00,671 --> 00:17:03,172
Oh, of course.
I'm sure. It's just...

289
00:17:05,509 --> 00:17:08,411
I'm breaking
a lot of my rules
seeing a divorced man.

290
00:17:10,113 --> 00:17:13,182
But Jane has made you
her personal cause.

291
00:17:14,984 --> 00:17:18,119
And there are so many
real problems in the world.

292
00:17:19,622 --> 00:17:21,289
I know.

293
00:17:21,357 --> 00:17:23,758
The world is so dark right now.

294
00:17:23,825 --> 00:17:26,493
The country?

295
00:17:26,561 --> 00:17:30,330
My goodness,
you've made me feel very
serious all of a sudden.

296
00:17:32,467 --> 00:17:34,868
I don't know if I can make you
feel better about the world.

297
00:17:34,936 --> 00:17:37,171
One of the boys killed
in Mississippi...

298
00:17:37,239 --> 00:17:40,041
Andrew Goodman,
he was from here.

299
00:17:40,109 --> 00:17:42,578
A girlfriend of mine
knew him from summer camp.

300
00:17:42,645 --> 00:17:46,382
Is that what it takes
to change things?

301
00:17:49,487 --> 00:17:51,221
What do you do?

302
00:17:51,289 --> 00:17:53,724
I'm an actress.

303
00:17:53,792 --> 00:17:56,060
But right now I'm a super
in the opera.

304
00:17:56,127 --> 00:17:59,497
- And what is that?
- A supernumerary.

305
00:17:59,565 --> 00:18:02,133
We're the actors
that fill the stage.

306
00:18:02,201 --> 00:18:04,269
Like the chorus?

307
00:18:04,337 --> 00:18:06,204
Mmm, no singing.

308
00:18:06,272 --> 00:18:07,939
I do a lot of mock drinking.

309
00:18:08,007 --> 00:18:10,375
I'm a wench.
I'm a...

310
00:18:10,443 --> 00:18:12,476
Courtesan.

311
00:18:12,544 --> 00:18:15,814
Part of a harem.
It depends on the opera.

312
00:18:17,283 --> 00:18:19,417
That is truly fascinating.

313
00:18:20,686 --> 00:18:22,688
I love the music.

314
00:18:22,755 --> 00:18:25,624
And I love backstage.

315
00:18:25,692 --> 00:18:28,962
Our costumes are as good
as the singers.

316
00:18:29,029 --> 00:18:31,231
And I love the stories.

317
00:18:31,298 --> 00:18:33,934
They're very romantic.

318
00:18:34,002 --> 00:18:35,836
Have you been?

319
00:18:35,903 --> 00:18:37,804
I have.

320
00:18:37,871 --> 00:18:41,573
But only for business
so I've never enjoyed it.

321
00:18:41,641 --> 00:18:44,176
Well, then you must
come as my guest.

322
00:18:46,546 --> 00:18:49,281
They give the supers tickets
instead of paying
a decent wage.

323
00:18:51,384 --> 00:18:52,984
- Madam?
- Oh, I don't even
need to look.

324
00:18:53,052 --> 00:18:54,686
Chicken Kiev.

325
00:18:54,754 --> 00:18:56,421
They make you wear a bib.

326
00:18:56,489 --> 00:18:59,358
Come on, let's have some fun.

327
00:19:00,493 --> 00:19:02,128
Two chicken Kievs.

328
00:19:11,406 --> 00:19:13,075
The barbizon.

329
00:19:13,142 --> 00:19:14,877
I bet that would
make a great opera.

330
00:19:14,944 --> 00:19:17,179
It would.

331
00:19:17,247 --> 00:19:19,848
Well, I guess
this is good night.

332
00:19:19,916 --> 00:19:22,385
Okay.

333
00:19:24,622 --> 00:19:26,223
Good night.

334
00:19:28,393 --> 00:19:31,395
So am I going to see you
at Roger and Jane's
for Thanksgiving?

335
00:19:33,731 --> 00:19:35,732
It's tempting, but...

336
00:19:35,799 --> 00:19:37,867
I have plans.

337
00:19:37,935 --> 00:19:41,136
Oh, I'm sure the holidays
must be very complex.

338
00:19:58,086 --> 00:20:01,855
It may have been awhile
since you've had to pick up
on messages,

339
00:20:01,922 --> 00:20:05,124
But I want to see you again.

340
00:20:05,192 --> 00:20:07,359
How about right now?

341
00:20:07,427 --> 00:20:09,528
I stopped the meter.
We can start it again.

342
00:20:09,595 --> 00:20:11,497
It'll be like
I just picked you up.

343
00:20:11,564 --> 00:20:13,432
Will you please take a weak no?

344
00:20:15,502 --> 00:20:17,737
Let's see where
we are new year's eve.

345
00:20:17,804 --> 00:20:20,873
- If it's meant
to be, it'll keep.
- Let me walk you in.

346
00:20:20,941 --> 00:20:22,709
No.

347
00:20:22,777 --> 00:20:24,945
I know that trick.

348
00:20:48,301 --> 00:20:50,903
Waverly and 6th Avenue.

349
00:20:54,643 --> 00:20:56,911
I think you both really
acquitted yourselves well.

350
00:20:56,979 --> 00:21:00,148
She doesn't know when to stop.
You don't know when to stop.

351
00:21:00,215 --> 00:21:02,884
My objective
was to get the ham.

352
00:21:02,952 --> 00:21:04,619
No one told you to hit me.

353
00:21:04,687 --> 00:21:06,588
That wasn't part of it.

354
00:21:06,655 --> 00:21:09,924
The important thing is that...
oh, here's Mr. Campbell.

355
00:21:12,928 --> 00:21:15,496
I've been assured you ladies
can look for your names

356
00:21:15,564 --> 00:21:18,132
And perhaps your picture
in Monday's "daily news."

357
00:21:18,200 --> 00:21:21,569
- What section?
- It's the "daily news."
it's one big section.

358
00:21:23,238 --> 00:21:26,674
All in all,
not a bad way
to spend a Sunday.

359
00:21:28,711 --> 00:21:31,078
Can you go back to the market
and get me some aspirin?

360
00:21:31,146 --> 00:21:33,947
We probably shouldn't have any
more contact for the time being.

361
00:21:35,817 --> 00:21:37,284
<i>- shall we?</i>

362
00:21:41,988 --> 00:21:43,956
We really appreciate
your talent

363
00:21:44,023 --> 00:21:45,958
And of course, your discretion.

364
00:21:46,025 --> 00:21:47,559
- You hurt me.
- Ow ow ow!

365
00:21:47,627 --> 00:21:49,561
Ladies, ladies, ladies!

366
00:21:49,629 --> 00:21:53,131
- Daisy!
- Walk her to the train.

367
00:21:55,735 --> 00:21:57,036
- Are you okay, dear?
- Yeah.

368
00:21:58,672 --> 00:22:00,540
Let's get you in a cab.

369
00:22:05,380 --> 00:22:08,249
- Good morning.
- Welcome back.
How was Los Angeles?

370
00:22:08,317 --> 00:22:09,984
Very hard to leave.

371
00:22:10,052 --> 00:22:12,887
I would love a vacation.

372
00:22:12,955 --> 00:22:14,690
It wasn't a vacation.

373
00:22:14,757 --> 00:22:16,859
I had a lot of tsuris
with Lucy and Desi.

374
00:22:16,926 --> 00:22:18,861
Has someone been
using my office?

375
00:22:18,928 --> 00:22:20,629
Mr. Sterling doesn't
have a television.

376
00:22:20,697 --> 00:22:22,965
I'm calling
a meeting for 11:00.

377
00:22:23,033 --> 00:22:25,268
No, make it 1:00.
Do we have a table yet?

378
00:22:25,336 --> 00:22:27,504
1:30 and no.

379
00:22:28,739 --> 00:22:31,208
- Hi.
- Yes?

380
00:22:31,275 --> 00:22:33,377
<i>- Do you know where
the seacore rough cut is?
I got it!</i>

381
00:22:36,014 --> 00:22:38,682
Don't you want to know why?

382
00:22:38,750 --> 00:22:40,918
I sold the jai alai TV special.

383
00:22:40,986 --> 00:22:43,154
Really?

384
00:22:43,221 --> 00:22:45,022
A.B.C.
They're moving towards

385
00:22:45,090 --> 00:22:47,091
All these eccentric
sporting events... go-karts.

386
00:22:47,159 --> 00:22:49,460
Well, that's very exciting.

387
00:22:49,528 --> 00:22:51,529
Can you get someone to track
down a cup of coffee for me?

388
00:22:51,597 --> 00:22:53,665
And I'd love
a grapefruit juice.
And, Joan?

389
00:22:53,732 --> 00:22:57,335
- That is my news.
- I won't even tell people
after it's aired.

390
00:23:02,408 --> 00:23:03,875
Good morning,
Mr. Draper.

391
00:23:05,711 --> 00:23:07,912
Don, can I speak
with you for a minute?

392
00:23:14,953 --> 00:23:17,422
Morning.

393
00:23:17,490 --> 00:23:19,891
- Lane, would you
excuse us for a minute?
- Of course.

394
00:23:19,959 --> 00:23:21,793
Good morning, don.

395
00:23:27,267 --> 00:23:29,402
You know,

396
00:23:29,469 --> 00:23:32,005
No one who's ever been
associated with an actual event

397
00:23:32,072 --> 00:23:34,707
Has thought it's been portrayed
honestly in the newspaper.

398
00:23:38,646 --> 00:23:41,014
"Donald draper,
or don as he is known"

399
00:23:41,081 --> 00:23:44,317
Perhaps in an attempt
to appear humble,
is a handsome cipher.

400
00:23:46,320 --> 00:23:48,188
One imagines somewhere
in an attic

401
00:23:48,255 --> 00:23:50,457
"There's a painting of him
that's rapidly aging."

402
00:23:52,026 --> 00:23:54,027
For a guy from "ad age"
he can really write.

403
00:23:54,095 --> 00:23:56,630
- He also says you're married.
- Jesus.

404
00:23:56,698 --> 00:23:59,533
He never asked me that.
Did he check any facts?

405
00:23:59,601 --> 00:24:01,568
You didn't give him any facts.

406
00:24:01,636 --> 00:24:05,272
- He had to make
some assumptions.
- My job is to write ads,

407
00:24:05,340 --> 00:24:07,341
Not go around
talking about who I am.

408
00:24:07,409 --> 00:24:09,443
Who knows who you are?

409
00:24:09,511 --> 00:24:12,547
This was supposed to be
an advertisement for the firm.

410
00:24:12,615 --> 00:24:14,415
Why do you have so many copies?

411
00:24:14,483 --> 00:24:16,350
I bought one to read.

412
00:24:16,418 --> 00:24:19,187
I was going to buy one
to frame in reception,
and then I read it.

413
00:24:19,254 --> 00:24:21,656
I just wanted
to get them all
before anyone else did.

414
00:24:21,723 --> 00:24:23,758
It'll be lining bird cages
by Friday.

415
00:24:23,826 --> 00:24:26,194
This is a missed opportunity.

416
00:24:26,261 --> 00:24:29,130
You turned all the sizzle
from glo-coat into a wet fart.

417
00:24:29,198 --> 00:24:31,365
Plus you sound like a prick.

418
00:24:31,433 --> 00:24:33,434
Well, it's done.

419
00:24:36,404 --> 00:24:38,405
Stay away from
one-legged reporters.

420
00:24:38,473 --> 00:24:40,140
Yeah, I was thinking
about that...

421
00:24:40,208 --> 00:24:42,576
Who is he to criticize anybody?

422
00:24:42,644 --> 00:24:46,647
Just so you
don't kill yourself,
there was some good news.

423
00:24:46,714 --> 00:24:48,649
Jane's friend found
you to be charming.

424
00:24:48,717 --> 00:24:50,484
Although a little
grabby in the car.

425
00:24:50,552 --> 00:24:52,920
That is good news.
Thank you.

426
00:24:52,988 --> 00:24:55,356
She liked you.
Maybe you should have
fondled peg-leg Pete.

427
00:24:55,424 --> 00:24:57,459
They raise you up
and they knock you down.

428
00:24:57,527 --> 00:24:59,894
I don't know what
I could have done differently.

429
00:24:59,962 --> 00:25:02,730
I believe that you were
being modest, but he didn't.

430
00:25:02,798 --> 00:25:05,233
I'm sorry, but after
the year you've had,

431
00:25:05,301 --> 00:25:07,168
It's just not
appropriate anymore.

432
00:25:12,341 --> 00:25:13,908
He's expecting us!

433
00:25:15,477 --> 00:25:18,079
- Is Joey coming?
- I'm here.

434
00:25:18,147 --> 00:25:21,249
- Oh.
- Why can't you come
to our office?

435
00:25:21,317 --> 00:25:24,518
- Do you want to hear what
sugarberry said or not?
- Shoot.

436
00:25:24,586 --> 00:25:27,888
It was uproarious.
First it's Darryl,
and he tells me about

437
00:25:27,956 --> 00:25:31,125
How they stared at
the article all day yesterday
worrying about a lawsuit.

438
00:25:31,192 --> 00:25:33,328
So I hang up and debate
whether or not to tell don...

439
00:25:33,395 --> 00:25:35,730
Throw myself on my sword.
And then Kreutzer calls

440
00:25:35,798 --> 00:25:37,832
<i>To tell me other papers
picked up the story.</i>

441
00:25:37,900 --> 00:25:40,034
<i>And I think,
"he knows it's us,"
but how could he?</i>

442
00:25:40,102 --> 00:25:43,571
And he said everyone,
especially Darryl,
was very excited.

443
00:25:46,008 --> 00:25:48,176
He's sorry someone got hurt,

444
00:25:48,244 --> 00:25:50,345
But more people will
taste their ham now

445
00:25:50,413 --> 00:25:52,581
And they'll love it.

446
00:25:52,649 --> 00:25:55,650
It's beautiful.
How do you put something
like this in your book?

447
00:25:55,718 --> 00:25:57,519
You can't.
We can't even
charge them.

448
00:25:57,587 --> 00:25:58,854
It wouldn't be a bad idea

449
00:25:58,922 --> 00:26:00,856
For them to increase
their media budget.

450
00:26:00,923 --> 00:26:03,358
- Seize the moment.
- With more crappy ads?

451
00:26:03,426 --> 00:26:05,593
- Hopefully not.
- You use it.

452
00:26:05,661 --> 00:26:09,430
The winner of
the ham battle is you.

453
00:26:09,498 --> 00:26:12,032
Can you imagine?
Lane's dentures would
drop out of his head

454
00:26:12,100 --> 00:26:13,701
If we came in
with an additional buy.

455
00:26:16,704 --> 00:26:19,273
"our hams are worth
fighting for."

456
00:26:21,476 --> 00:26:25,780
A cartoon pilgrim and an Indian
in a tug of war with the ham.

457
00:26:25,847 --> 00:26:28,649
Old ladies will smile.

458
00:26:28,717 --> 00:26:31,518
Why didn't you pitch
that two months ago?
It's good on its own.

459
00:26:31,586 --> 00:26:33,621
A slogan's nothing
when you have a good idea.

460
00:26:35,223 --> 00:26:37,257
Black crayon.
I need it in an hour.

461
00:26:37,325 --> 00:26:39,159
Chop chop, Joey.

462
00:26:41,429 --> 00:26:43,798
Clara, could you get Darryl
for me at sugarberry?

463
00:26:43,866 --> 00:26:46,834
Tell him it's urgent.
I may need you.

464
00:26:48,737 --> 00:26:50,938
<i>Horace cook, Jr.
It's urgent.</i>

465
00:26:52,174 --> 00:26:54,976
Ho-ho!
How was Tijuana?

466
00:26:55,043 --> 00:26:58,346
I have to say,
it's a very flattering
picture.

467
00:26:58,414 --> 00:27:01,316
And I don't think
I'd mind being
described that way.

468
00:27:01,383 --> 00:27:03,317
Mr. Crane,
you're a salesman.

469
00:27:03,385 --> 00:27:06,187
You do not want to be
known as mysterious.

470
00:27:06,255 --> 00:27:08,122
There'll be
no further discussion.

471
00:27:08,190 --> 00:27:10,625
I just got off
the phone with ho-ho.

472
00:27:10,693 --> 00:27:13,127
- Jai alai is leaving.
- What?

473
00:27:13,195 --> 00:27:16,964
- It's over.
- Bullshit. I just sold
a TV special to a.B.C.

474
00:27:17,032 --> 00:27:20,301
Well, apparently don didn't
mention them in the article.

475
00:27:22,104 --> 00:27:24,706
I didn't mention anyone.
That's the reporter's job.

476
00:27:27,676 --> 00:27:30,878
- Spectacular.
- What the hell's ho-ho
doing reading "ad age"?

477
00:27:30,946 --> 00:27:33,314
- Fix it.
- Todd got all the partners

478
00:27:33,382 --> 00:27:36,117
From c.G.C. To call and they
worked him up and down.

479
00:27:36,185 --> 00:27:37,652
They told him
we laugh about him.

480
00:27:37,720 --> 00:27:39,687
I don't!
Get him him on the phone,

481
00:27:39,755 --> 00:27:42,056
Get him in here
or camp out in his driveway.

482
00:27:42,124 --> 00:27:44,926
He hung up on me.

483
00:27:44,993 --> 00:27:47,662
I think he was crying.

484
00:27:49,398 --> 00:27:52,233
How much was left in
ho-ho anyway?

485
00:27:52,300 --> 00:27:55,269
We'll survive with jai alai
off our list.

486
00:27:55,336 --> 00:27:57,604
We will survive,
but for how long?

487
00:27:57,672 --> 00:27:59,172
The loss of jai alai

