to be out a month ago.

638
00:39:35,628 --> 00:39:38,564
We haven't found the right
place for the kids.

639
00:39:38,632 --> 00:39:41,868
Well, either do as we agreed
or I'm going to need
to collect rent.

640
00:39:41,936 --> 00:39:45,138
- What?
- Or you could just buy it
from me if you want to.

641
00:39:45,206 --> 00:39:47,007
I can't believe you.

642
00:39:47,074 --> 00:39:49,609
Don, it's temporary.

643
00:39:49,677 --> 00:39:53,179
Believe me, Henry,
everybody thinks this
is temporary.

644
00:39:53,247 --> 00:39:55,514
Good night.

645
00:40:00,786 --> 00:40:03,188
He has some nerve.

646
00:40:03,255 --> 00:40:05,690
I know you don't want
to hear this,

647
00:40:05,757 --> 00:40:08,225
But he's right.

648
00:40:08,293 --> 00:40:11,228
Haven't the kids been
through enough change
already?

649
00:40:11,295 --> 00:40:13,964
I can't just uproot them
with no place to go.

650
00:40:14,031 --> 00:40:16,432
You're not even looking.

651
00:40:16,500 --> 00:40:18,901
There's nothing out there,
and he doesn't decide.

652
00:40:29,545 --> 00:40:31,947
<i>- miss Olson is here
to see you.</i>

653
00:40:37,154 --> 00:40:39,056
Send her in.

654
00:40:44,663 --> 00:40:46,397
They sent one for each of us.

655
00:40:48,634 --> 00:40:50,868
Could have just as easily
fired us.

656
00:40:50,936 --> 00:40:54,106
But they didn't
because they sold
more hams.

657
00:40:54,173 --> 00:40:57,143
And now you get
to tell them why,
if you want.

658
00:40:57,210 --> 00:40:58,477
I think they'll be impressed.

659
00:41:00,514 --> 00:41:01,614
Well, I'm not.

660
00:41:03,685 --> 00:41:06,019
